# =============================================================================
# DATABASE — required for DealArada (login, products, orders, admin, etc.)
# =============================================================================
#
# You must set EXACTLY ONE of these to your NEON POOLED connection string.
# (The app reads POSTGRES_URL first, then DATABASE_URL — same value for both is fine.)
#
#   POSTGRES_URL=postgresql://...
#   DATABASE_URL=postgresql://...
#
# How to get the POOLED value (Neon):
#   1. Open https://console.neon.tech and select your project.
#   2. Click "Connection details" (or the connect / dashboard widget).
#   3. Choose the POOLED / POOLER / "Serverless" option — the hostname usually
#      contains "-pooler" (e.g. ep-xxxx-pooler.region.aws.neon.tech).
#   4. Copy the full postgresql://... string and paste it on ONE line below.
#
# Where to put it (pick one):
#   • BEST: Create a file named ".env.local" in THIS folder (dealarada/) and add
#     the line there. Next.js loads it automatically; it should not be committed.
#   • OR: Add the line to ".env" in this folder (already used for other flags).
#
# After saving: stop the dev server (Ctrl+C), then run "npm run dev" or dev.cmd again.
#
# =============================================================================
# Split deploy: Vercel = frontend, Render = backend (API + DB)
# =============================================================================
#
# On VERCEL (this Next.js app only — no Postgres required if every /api call is proxied):
#
#   1. Project → Settings → Environment Variables
#   2. Add BACKEND_API_URL = your Render web service origin, e.g.
#        https://dealarada-xxxx.onrender.com
#      Use the HTTPS URL from Render’s dashboard. No trailing slash. Do NOT add /api
#      (the app appends /api/... itself).
#   3. Add BACKEND_API_URL for "Production" and "Preview" if you use preview deploys.
#   4. Redeploy after saving env vars — rewrites are applied at build time.
#   5. Optional: NEXT_PUBLIC_GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY (same as below) if you need maps.
#   6. You do NOT need POSTGRES_URL on Vercel when BACKEND_API_URL is set (API runs on Render).
#
# On RENDER (full Node server running this same repo / start command):
#
#   • Set POSTGRES_URL or DATABASE_URL (Neon pooled URL).
#   • Do NOT set BACKEND_API_URL on Render.
#
# Local dev with a remote API (optional):
#   • In .env.local set BACKEND_API_URL=https://your-service.onrender.com
#   • Then `npm run dev` proxies /api/* to Render (next.config rewrites).
#
# =============================================================================
# DATABASE — required on Render (or any full-stack deploy without BACKEND_API_URL)
# =============================================================================

POSTGRES_URL=

# If you prefer Vercel’s name for the same Neon URL, use this instead of POSTGRES_URL:
# DATABASE_URL=

# =============================================================================
# Optional — Google Maps (track page live rider map)
# =============================================================================
# Enable "Maps JavaScript API" in Google Cloud Console, create an API key,
# restrict it by HTTP referrer (your domain + localhost for dev).
# NEXT_PUBLIC_GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY=

# =============================================================================
# Vercel frontend only — proxy /api to Render (see section above)
# =============================================================================
# BACKEND_API_URL=https://your-service.onrender.com

# =============================================================================
# Optional — file uploads (@vercel/blob). Needed for /api/upload on Vercel builds;
# on Render-only API, configure the token on Render instead if you use Blob there.
# =============================================================================
# BLOB_READ_WRITE_TOKEN=

# =============================================================================
# Security / production notes (no extra vars required)
# =============================================================================
# • Session cookie: httpOnly, SameSite=Lax, Secure in NODE_ENV=production.
# • New signups use scrypt password hashes (Node crypto); demo seed users use
#   demo:… format — remove or avoid demo routes in real production DB hygiene.
# • POST /api/auth/reset-demo and /api/auth/reset-seller are disabled when
#   NODE_ENV=production (returns 404).
# • Only NEXT_PUBLIC_* is exposed to the browser (e.g. Maps key). Never put
#   database URLs or blob tokens in NEXT_PUBLIC_*.
